Assembly using MegaHit

filtering reads and removing host genome sequences has been performed from the processing steps. You now have a high quality filtered reads in FASTQ format and we can proceed with the Assembly step using MEGAHIT

Install megahit: 

code: sudo apt install megahit

Your FASTQ files -non_human_cleaned.fq are in the directory

RUN Megahit: 


code: megahit -1 /mnt/e/X401SC24100039-Z01-F001_03/01.RawData/AA_0126/non_human_cleaned_1.fq \
        -2 /mnt/e/X401SC24100039-Z01-F001_03/01.RawData/AA_0126/non_human_cleaned_2.fq \
        -o /mnt/e/X401SC24100039-Z01-F001_03/01.RawData/AA_0126/assembly_output

you will receive contigs (assembled sequences) in the output directory usually named final.contigs.ga

i install GNU parallel, to run MEGAHIT in parallel across two folders with a single non-human-cleaned fq file in each AA_XXXX folder,
code: sudo apt-get install parallel

i set up an output directory for /mnt/e/X401SC24100039-Z01-F001_02
code: mkdir -p /mnt/e/MEGAHIT_results

Here is the list of commands to process each folder. 

Code: find /mnt/e/X401SC24100039-Z01-F001_02/01.RawData/AA_* \
    
     -type d | while read folder; do
    # Extract the folder name
    sample_name=$(basename $folder)

    # Find the non-human cleaned FASTQ file
    fq_file=$(find $folder -type f -name "*.fq" | grep -E "non_human_cleaned.fq")

    # Check if the FASTQ file exists
    if [ -n "$fq_file" ]; then
        echo "megahit -r $fq_file -o /mnt/e/MEGAHIT_results/${sample_name} --num-cpu-threads 4 --memory 28000"
    else
        echo "echo 'No non-human cleaned FASTQ file found in $folder. Skipping...'"
    fi
done > megahit_job_list.txt

To run jobs in parallel 
parallel -j 4< megahit_job_list.txt

code: 
#!/bin/bash
#SBATCH --job-name=megahit_job  # Job name
#SBATCH --output=megahit_%j.out  # Standard output log
#SBATCH --error=megahit_%j.err  # Standard error log
#SBATCH --ntasks=1  # Number of tasks
#SBATCH --cpus-per-task=4  # Number of CPU cores per task
#SBATCH --mem=32GB  # Memory per node
#SBATCH --time=24:00:00  # Time limit (24 hours)

module load megahit

for folder in /scratch/your_project_name/AA_*/; do
    fq="$folder/non_human_cleaned.fq"
    if [ -f "$fq" ]; then
        megahit -r "$fq" -o "$folder/megahit_output" --num-cpu-threads $SLURM_CPUS_PER_TASK
    fi
done

this is used on X401SC24100039-Z01-F001_03 where the megahit_output is located in each and every folder for AA_XXXX

some of the files (eg: AA_0008) does not have an output.sam, rerun your bowtie2 and perform SAM filtering and then extract your non human reads. 

theres a possibility that MEGAHIT might overwrite completed assemblies and will skip them by default unless -o specifies an overwrite. you might have to rerun a couple of times
